'''Jassem Gaber El-Sayed Abdulsalam''' ({{langx|ar|جَاسِم جَابِر السَّيِّد عَبْد السَّلَام}}; born 20 February 2002) is a [[Qatari]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] or [[defensive midfielder]] for Qatari club [[Al-Rayyan SC|Al-Rayyan]] and the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].<ref name="SW"/>

==Club career==
In January 2020, Gaber signed a four-year contract to remain with [[Al-Arabi SC (Qatar)|Al-Arabi]] until the 2024 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=898806 |title=العربي يؤمن بقاء جاسم جابر حتى 2024 |trans-title=Al-Arabi believes that Jassem Gaber will remain until 2024 |website=Kooora.com |date=25 February 2020 |access-date=17 November 2022}}</ref>

In January 2022, Gaber was included in the [[International Federation of Football History & Statistics|IFFHS]] AFC Under-20 Team of the Year for 2021.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iffhs.com/posts/1558 |title=IFFHS Men's Youth Continental Teams of the Year 2021 – AFC |publisher=[[International Federation of Football History & Statistics]] |date=3 January 2022 |access-date=17 November 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Titaoui |first=Amer |url=https://www.royasport.com/?p=4008 |title=لاعب العربي جاسم جابر ضمن أفضل تشكيلة آسيوية شابة |trans-title=Al-Arabi player Jassem Jaber is among the best young Asian squad |work=Roya Sports |date=4 January 2022 |access-date=17 November 2022 |language=ar}}</ref>

==International career==
Gaber made his debut for [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]] in 2022. He was selected for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] that was hosted in his home country Qatar.<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/qatar-squad-announcement-fifa-world-cup-2022 Hosts Qatar announce 26-man World Cup squad] FIFA. Retrieved 13 November 2022.</ref>

In January 2024, Gaber was named in Qatar's 26-men squad for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Our final list for Asia 🏆|url=https://twitter.com/QFA_EN/status/1742493635214454878|publisher=Qatar Football Association|website=Twitter|date=3 January 2024|access-date=3 January 2024}}</ref> In the semi-finals game against [[Iran national football team|Iran]], he scored the 1–1 equalizer goal from a shot outside the penalty area, as the match later ended in a 3–2 win for Qatar, which qualified them to the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup final|final]].<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2024/2/7/qatar-edge-iran-3-2-in-dramatic-asian-cup-2023-semifinal Qatar edge Iran 3-2 in dramatic Asian Cup 2023 semifinal] Al Jazeera. Retrieved 10 February 2024.</ref>

